President Joe Biden has announced his nominees for key positions in climate and transportation across various government agencies. The nominees include Tommy Beaudreau for Deputy Secretary of the Interior, Meera Joshi for Administrator of the Federal Motor Carrier Safety Administration, Faisal Amin for Chief Financial Officer of the Environmental Protection Agency, Christopher Coes for Assistant Secretary for Transportation Policy at the Department of Transportation, Shannon Estenoz for Assistant Secretary for Fish and Wildlife and Parks at the Department of the Interior, Radhika Fox for Assistant Administrator for Water at the Environmental Protection Agency, Michal Freedhoff for Assistant Administrator for Chemical Safety and Pollution Prevention at the Environmental Protection Agency, Jill Hruby for Under Secretary for Nuclear Security and Administrator of the National Nuclear Security Administration at the Department of Energy, Winnie Stachelberg for Assistant Secretary for Policy, Management, and Budget at the Department of the Interior, and Tanya Trujillo for Assistant Secretary for Water and Science at the Department of the Interior. The nominees have backgrounds in areas such as law, government oversight, finance, transportation policy, and environmental management.